rules: Rule1: Either animal1 undergoes veterinarian review or animal1 undergoes lab analysis.
Rule2: Whenever animal1 undergoes lab analysis, if animal1 does not show symptoms or test positive, then animal1 does not require treatment.
Rule3: If animal1 undergoes first inspection, then animal1 is not approved for release.
Rule4: Under the condition that animal1 undergoes second inspection, animal1 is not approved for release.
Rule5: Whenever animal1 undergoes senior veterinarian review, animal1 undergoes first inspection.
Rule6: Either animal1 undergoes senior veterinarian review or animal1 receives health board approval.
Rule7: If animal1 receives health board approval, then animal1 undergoes second inspection.
Rule8: Provided that animal1's quarantine is extended, it is not the case that animal1 completes isolation period.
Rule9: If animal1 has conflicting reports, then animal1 is safe to release.
Rule10: Either animal1 has conflicting reports or animal1's quarantine is extended.
Rule11: Under the condition that animal1's investigation is complete, if it is not the case that conflicting reports imply animal1 is not safe to release, then animal1 requires investigation.
Rule12: Animal1 undergoes special committee review or animal1's investigation is complete.
Rule13: If animal1 receives government clearance, then animal1 meets quarantine condition.
Rule14: Whenever animal1 receives diplomatic clearance, if the absence of government clearance does not imply animal1 has export restriction, then animal1 does not undergo international transport.
Rule15: If animal1 is in an emergency situation, then animal1 is immediately released.
Rule16: Under the condition that animal1 undergoes enhanced monitoring, animal1 is not immediately released.
Rule17: If animal1 has outbreak risk, then, given that animal1 is in an emergency situation, animal1 undergoes enhanced monitoring.
Rule18: Either animal1 has outbreak risk or animal1 has zoonotic potential.
Rule19: If animal1 has zoonotic potential, then animal1 has pandemic concern.
Rule20: Whenever animal1 has pandemic concern, under the condition that animal1 is in an emergency situation, animal1 undergoes enhanced monitoring.
Rule21: Either animal1 undergoes standard procedure or animal1 shows symptoms or tests positive.
Rule22: If animal1 undergoes fast-track review, then animal1 does not undergo standard procedure.
Rule23: If animal1 undergoes domestic transport, then animal1 is for local sale only.
Rule24: Under the condition that animal1 undergoes regional distribution, animal1 undergoes inter-state transfer.
Rule25: Either animal1 receives full clearance or, if animal1 undergoes inter-state transfer, then animal1 undergoes domestic transport.
Rule26: Either animal1 undergoes preliminary screening or animal1 undergoes detailed examination.
Rule27: Whenever animal1 undergoes detailed examination, animal1 does not undergo normal processing.
Rule28: If animal1 has conflicting findings, then animal1 has contamination suspected.
Rule29: Whenever animal1 has conflicting findings, it is not the case that animal1 has biohazard risk.

Rule30: Either animal1 has conflicting findings or, if animal1 undergoes comprehensive assessment, then, under the condition that animal1 undergoes preliminary screening, animal1 does not undergo normal processing.
Rule31: If animal1 has pathogen detected, then animal1 has biohazard risk.
Rule32: Provided that animal1 has contamination suspected, animal1 has pathogen detected.

Rule33: Either animal1 is cleared or animal1 is in quarantine or, if it is not the case that animal1 has a disease or (if animal1 does not meet quarantine condition, then animal1 has authorization), then animal1 is not released.
Rule34: Whenever animal1 shows symptoms, if animal1 does not meet quarantine condition, then animal1 is not healthy.
Rule35: Provided that animal1 tests positive, under the condition that animal1 does not meet quarantine condition, animal1 is not healthy.
Rule36: If it is not the case that veterinarian review implies (if animal1 does not show symptoms or test positive, then animal1 does not require treatment), then animal1 is approved for release.
Rule37: If it is not the case that conflicting reports imply animal1 is not safe to release, then animal1 does not require investigation.
Rule38: Provided that it is not the case that animal1 has a disease or (if animal1 does not meet quarantine condition, then animal1 has authorization), animal1 is released.
Rule39: If it is not the case that emergency situation implies enhanced monitoring, then animal1 undergoes normal processing.
Rule40: If it is not the case that trade embargo implies animal1 does not have export restriction, then animal1 undergoes regional distribution.
Rule41: Under the condition that it is not the case that trade embargo implies animal1 does not have export restriction, animal1 is not for local sale only.
Rule42: Whenever animal1 does not show symptoms or test positive, animal1 requires treatment.
Rule43: Provided that it is not the case that the absence of government clearance implies animal1 does not have export restriction, animal1 undergoes international transport.
Rule44: If animal1 does not receive government clearance, then animal1 has export restriction.
Rule45: Under the condition that animal1 does not receive government clearance, animal1 faces trade embargo.
Rule46: If animal1 does not meet quarantine condition, then animal1 completes isolation period.
Rule47: Under the condition that animal1 does not meet quarantine condition, animal1 is in an emergency situation.
Rule48: Provided that animal1 does not meet quarantine condition, animal1 is healthy.
Rule49: Whenever animal1 does not meet quarantine condition, animal1 does not have authorization.
facts: Fact4: Animal1 does not have a disease.
Fact5: Animal1 does not undergo special committee review.
Fact6: Animal1 is not in quarantine.
Fact7: Animal1 does not receive full clearance.
